###
### PhotoTribe API templates for VS Code REST Client
### Select environment in REST Client: dev | test | prod
### Uses variables from ./rest-client.env.json
###

@baseUrl = {{baseUrl}}
@jwt = {{jwt}}
@username = {{username}}
@email = {{email}}
@password = {{password}}
@photoId = {{photoId}}

### DEV - Register (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### TEST - Register (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### PROD - Register (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### DEV - Login (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### DEV - Get Photos (GET)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/photos

### DEV - Upload Photo (POST multipart)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/photos/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=PhotoBoundary

--PhotoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

REST Template Upload
--PhotoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

Uploaded using API template.
--PhotoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./sample.jpg
--PhotoBoundary--

### DEV - Replace Photo (PUT) [template endpoint, update as needed]
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/photos/{{photoId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated title",
  "description": "Updated via PUT"
}

### DEV - Partial Update Photo (PATCH) [template endpoint, update as needed]
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/photos/{{photoId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Updated via PATCH"
}

### DEV - Delete Photo (DELETE) [template endpoint, update as needed]
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/photos/{{photoId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwt}}

### DEV - Options on Photos (OPTIONS)
OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/api/photos
Origin: http://localhost:5173
Access-Control-Request-Method: GET

### DEV - Head on Photos (HEAD)
HEAD {{baseUrl}}/api/photos

### TEST - Get Photos (GET)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/photos

### TEST - Login (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### PROD - Get Photos (GET)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/photos

### PROD - Login (POST)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}